SampleComment: Wind Speed: 6km/h S. Wave Height: 0.2 m. Calm day with no winds. Birds: Loons, pelicans. Coyote howled nearby. Minnows present at dock. Zooplankton net off by 1 meter (less). Microcystin ID: M220044. Probe: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 12km/h W. Waves: 0.05 m. Profile sampled every 0.5 m until through thermocline then every 3 m until 4-5 m from bottom. Boat kept drifting away by strong wind (50 m). Rain clouds approaching later. Unable to document redox at 48.5, 48.0, 49.5 due to unexpected boat drift. Zoolankton depth adjusted due to unexpected drift and wind condition. Microcystin ID: M220043. Probe: 17B03383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 5km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.1m. Metal Sampling. Sediment sampling. 2 bald eagles, 1 osprey sighted. More scums on surface (during horizontal AIS hauls) than bottom/vertical depths. Rain a little at the end. Microcystin ID: M220042. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03523 and 22SWE03524.
Wind Speed: 7km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.0m. Heard ravens, saw a bald eagle (juvenile). Very sunny and calm day. Microcystin ID: M220041. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
surface grab - metals

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 8km/hr E. Wave Height: <0.01m. Beautiful, sunny day, the water was pretty calm during the profile sampling, the wind gust picked up to 12km/hr during the composite sampling, there was quite a bit of rainfall the last few days - Volunteer said the lake was pretty clear a couple days ago and could almost see lake bottom, there were a lot of pelicans at a variety of locations around the lake and some nesting grebes on the shoreline, not many other boaters out. Microcystin ID: M220072. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 20km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.20m. Warm, sunny day but quite windy, picked up to 24km/hr after the profile sample and was forcasted to get up to 29km/hr in the afternoon so could not complete the composite sampling, zooplankton and AIS were collected at the profile. The lake was quite foamy and observed some cyanobacteria particles near the surface. They said the area has recieved a good amount of rain this month. Saw some pelicans and gulls. *Could not re-schedule this trip due to time constraints. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 6km/hr E. Wave Height: <0.05m. Warm day, appeared to be a little hazy but there was no smell of smoke, observed some particles of cyanobacteria but no scum or blooms, the water was less green near the AIS beach locations than at profile. Not much precipitation in the area the last couple weeks, there has been a drawn out heat wave. Saw lots of pelicans still. Microcystin ID: M220070. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01307 and 22SWE01308.

Station: BUFFALO LAKE (NEAR BASHAW), MAIN BASIN COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 19km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.1m. Windy, partially sunny day on the lake, was able to keep the sonde and the tow net relatively straight through the profile, water appeared turbid but did not observe much presence of cyanobacteria blooms or larger species, no other boats were on the lake, weather has cooled down with frost advisories overnight. Microcystin ID: M220069. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 20km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.2m. It was windy at the beginning of the trip at the profile location but no rain or storms. The secchi disk fell off the chain and sunk to the bottom, so estimated the depth based on last year's secchi in June and also from observation of how long it took to disappear. Our boat drifted a bit from the profile location so the measurements are taken until 6.5m, where the bottom depth was closer to 7m. There were not many boats on the lake. The lake was a bit calmer while doing the composite sites but the wind picked up again at our last comp site. *New coordinates for profile measurements -53.478946, -114.255171. *Might have accidentally logged in at 7m where probe was likely in sediment. Microcystin ID: M220154. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 6km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.05m. The lake was very busy with boat rec users today, it was a clear, very hot day, the area has recieved a lot of rain and some storms in the last couple weeks. There was some cyanobacteria particles in the water but no visible blooms. Microcystin ID: M220153. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 31km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.05m. Overcast, windy day, the area has recieved a lot of precipitation and storms the last week, only a couple boats on the lake, did not observe any cyanobacteria blooms, saw some loons, took a metals sample grab at profile site as well as a sediment sample and QC samples. Microcystin ID: M220152. Probe #:17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01147 and 22SWE01148.

Wind Speed: Not recorded. Wave Height: 0.1m. Cool, overcast day. A storm came in halfway trhough our profile sampling and we were only able to collect data to 5m because the boat drifted from the profile location. A zooplankton sample was collected but could not start composite sampling. The lake had cyanobacteria particles present and appeared more green than previous sampling trips. There were no other boats on the lake. Sampling trip had to be re-scheduled. *Original fieldsheet was lost. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr W. Wave Height: <0.01m. Calm, sunny day, not much wind at all, launched from the public boat launch this time - observed a cyanobacteria bloom by the dock - the cyanobacteria was more prominent than any other sampling trip this seasonn and appeared to streak on the east to north end of the lake, but appeared more as particles on the south and west end, there were a couple other boats on the lake. *This was the re-scheduled trip from beginning of September. Microcystin ID: M220151. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 4km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.1-0.15m. Sunny day, wind picked up to 9km/hr - made using the tape and weight more difficult - relied mostly on depth finder on the boat for composite sites, there was no one else on the lake. Microcystin ID: M220146. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 7km/hr N. Wave Height: <0.01m. Beautiful, sunny day, it's been a hot dry week in the area, they said the lake recieved a heavy algae bloom last weekend that covered a lot of the lake, that was not as present during this trip except around the shoreline however there was a lot of cyanobacteria streaks observed trhough the whole lake. An AHS blue-green algae advisory has been posted since July 15. There was only one other boat on the lake with us. Microcystin ID: M220145. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 0km/hr N. Wave Height: <0.05m. Calm, sunny morning, no other boats were out. Volunteer said the lake has not been very busy this month, less scum observed on the surface this month than July, clarity was quite low, saw streaks of cyanobacteria trhoughout the lake, the area has not recieved much precipitation in the last couple weeks. Collected AIS, sediment, and QC samples. Microcystin ID: M220144. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC  Samples 22SWE01361 and 22SWE01362.

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: Wind Speed: 11km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.05m. Overcast, cooler day with a drizzle of rain, drifted a little from the profile location and reached a bottom depth of 16.5m - the lake appeared turbid and cyanobacteria particles were present near the surface but no scum spots, there were no other boats on the lake, there were streaks of cyanobacteria near the boat dock but did not have an odour as July/August did. Microcystin ID: M220143. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 7km/hr SE. Wave Height: <0.01m. Arrived to the lake and it was pouring rain and thundering, we waited about 20 mins and the storm passed. It was sunny, lots of lily pads, geese, pelicans, and ducks on the lake. Completed a full profile sample, the lake was calm. We noticed dark clouds coming in on our way to the 2nd comp site and the wind picked up quickly. We decided to dock at volunteer's acreage due to the waves and waited to see if the storm would pass quickly. The wind did not die down so we decided to re-schedule to Saturday. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 13km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.01m. Re-scheduled trip. It was suny and the lake was fairly calmer. There was a significant amount of rain the last couple days. The bottom depth was greater than the trip on Wednesday. Lots of poplar fluff present on the surface and pelicans. There were a couple people from the rowing club on the lake. We were unable to take the 7th comp sample at the very southern end of the lake, but took one more west of the 5th comp site. Microcystin ID: M220163. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 14km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.01m. There were a couple kayaks on the lake, it was more windy at the profile site but decreased through the comp sampling, saw some pelicans, the water level was a bit higher than June likely due to the significant amount of rain this summer. A bit of an overcast day, observed more lily pads near the rowing club dock. Microcystin ID: M220164. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 14km/hr W. Wave Height: 0.05m. Sunny, calm day on the lake, did not observe much cyanobaccteria in the lake. The samples collected were faily clear, saw some loons and pelicans. Collected AIS samples, QC samples for the lab and a sediment sample at the profile. Microcystin ID: M220165. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01214 and 22SWE01215.

Wind Speed: 13km/hr S. Wave height: 0.05m. Sunny day, a little bit of wind but a nice afternoon, did not observe any cyanobacteria blooms on the water or much particles in the water, lots of milfoil, bladderwort, and char throughout the lake. A couple other kayakers on the lake. Saw a muskrat on the water. Microcystin ID: M220016. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 11km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.05m. Very calm water, like glass - despite there being on/off rain, started raining a bit heavier during the comp samples. Wind picked up a little. Volunteer observed some algae in the water column, lake only had one other boat on it. Saw loons, pelicans, an osprey. Microcystin ID: M220142. Probe #: 17K04466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.05m. Nice day on the lake, lots of people on the dock. Some cyanobacteria present in the water, a big storm occured the night before and there was a lot of rain. *Some sediment appeared on the chlorophyll filters. Microcystin ID: M220141. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.05m. Hot, sunny day, the water had a higher clarity than July, a couple fishing boats on the lake. Saw an osprey, and some ducks. Took AIS, sediment, and QC samples. Beach was busy. Microcystin ID: 220140. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01284 and 22SWE01285.

Wind Speed: 20km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.05m. Sunny day, a little windy on the lake. Some blue-green algae observed at the surface. A couple fishing boats out. No chl-a result due to lab error. Microcystin ID: M220139. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.
Missed Trip - Volunteer scheduling issues

Wind Speed: 10km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.02m. 7.0m discrete grab collected because of metalimnetic uptick of oxygen detected from profile sampling. Microcystin and phytoplankton bottles filled with water from 7.0m. Microcystin ID: M220035. Microcystin ID (for discrete grab at 7.0m): M220113. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 19km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.2m. Sediment sampling. Metal sampling. Strong wind/boat drifting! Lots! Microcystin ID: M220034. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event invovled a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03413 and 22SWE03414.
Wind Speed: 13km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.02m. Wind picked up at 10:45am. Loons, vulture, gulls. Microcystin ID: M220033. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
Microcystin collected because of metalimnetic uptick of oxygen detected from profile sampling
surface grab - metals

Wind Speed: 13km/hr W. Wave height: 0.1m. Seen loons. Sunny day, the water was very calm, lots of pollen on the surface, decided to take 4 hauls of water at comp sites which ended up being close to just enough. Lake is stocked with Tiger Trout. Microcystin ID: M220126. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr E. Wave Height: <0.01. Surface Aerator running. Very overcast day but no rain while sampling, observed a lot more aquatic plants growing to the surface than the June sampling trip. There was an AHS blue-green algae advisory up near the provincial park boat launch. Observed cyanobacteria at the surface of the lake. The area has recieved a lot of precipitation the last week. There was a family of ducks on the lake with 13 ducklings. Volunteer noted a bit of an odour only near the Prov. Rec boat launch. Microcystin ID: M220125. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 5km/hr W. Wave Height: <0.01. Very hot, sunny afternoon, lake was calm, lots of weeds growing out from the public boat launch area. Observed lots of cyanobacteria throughout the lake. There was a slight odour - more distinguishable near the boat launch. Some canoes and paddleboards out. Blue-green advisory still posted - observed a little bit of blue-green by the boat launch. Lots of ducks on the lake. Collected AIS, sediment, and QC samples. Microcystin ID: M220124. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event invovled a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01273 and 22SWE01274.

Wind Speed: 6km/hr W. Wave Height: <0.01m. 1 Surface Aerator running year round, mid north side out 150m. The lake was calm, the sun was out but it was a bit hazy. There was another fishing boat on the lake. Cyanobacteria was present and blue-green algae was obsereved on the boat launch. The weeds were more prominent near the dock. Saw a couple moose on the shore. Microcystin ID: M220123. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 15km/hr N. Wave Height: 0.3m. Calm day, more windy/wavy on SW side of the lake; more calm at the main site. Bird: loon, terns, pelicans, goldeneye, western grebe. Microcystin ID: M220048. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
Wind Speed: 6km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.0m. Some cyano particles present on water. Birds: pelican, loon, grebe. Microcystin ID: M220047. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.01m. Sediment sample. Metal sample. Osprey, pelican, got windy as hour passed by. Microcystin ID: M220046. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event invovled a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03367 and 22SWE03368.
Wind Speed: 3km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.0m. Calm day. Colder water than other years. Microcystin ID: M220045. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 5km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.00m. Water went down by 1 foot. Birds: pelican. 2 far west composite sites not accessible with wakeboard boat (Franchere Basin). 8 composite sites visited. Microcystin ID: M220024. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 12km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.00m. Bottom depth shallower than last sampling date. Bird: pelican, loon, red necked grebe, Clark's grebe, tern, gull. Microcystin ID: M220023. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 14km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.3m. Metal sampling. QC sampling. Ekman dredge for sediment sample. Strong wind. Pelican, terns, gulls. Microcystin ID: M220022. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03253 and 22SWE03254.

Wind Speed: 4km/hr NE. Wave height: 0.00m. Blue green algae present. Grebes. Water level decreased by 2-3 inches. Not the deepest site (profile). Microcystin ID: M220021. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
surface grab - metals

Wind Speed: 10km/hr N. Wave Height: 0.00m. Calm day to start, thunderstorm approaching from the north later on. Birds: cormorant, grebe, pelican. Lots of tiny flying bugs. Microcystin ID: M220028. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
Wind Speed: 3km/hr N. Wave height: 0.00m. No rain past three weeks. Lot of wind past few weeks. Microcystin ID: M220027. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 13km/hr NW. Wave height: 0.05m. Metal sampling. Sediment sampling. Lake has dropped 0.5m since last sampling. No rain since last sampling. Microcystin ID: M220026. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03589 and 22SWE03590.
Wind Speed: 13km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.01m. Cormorants, trumpter swan. Slightly windy day. Water level went down since last month. Microcystin ID: M220025. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
top grab @ 1m. No snow survey collected as rains have diminished snow pack and created slush on ice surface. Secchi not collected. Zooplankton sample taken at 7.0m with an 8" tow net.
bottom grab @ 7m
Light not collected
only light recorded at this depth.  Par sensor readings start at this depth because this is the ice thickness
top grab @ 1m. Hardly no snow on ice, unable to collect snow survey this month. Some algae was visable in water this month (brownis/green). Zooplankton sample at 7.5m with an 8" tow net
bottom grab @ 7.5m
top grab @ 1m. Top few cm of ice is melting then solid clear ice all the way through. Sampled ~10m to East of bouy. Anoxic conditions at bottom, strong sulphur smell observed during bottom sample
bottom grab @ 7m
Partly cloudy with a light breeze. Colleted Surface at 10:00 MST and Bottom at 10:22 MST Metals and Hg samples.
Collected surface grab at 11:50 MST and bottom at 12:00 MST Metals and Hg samples. no secchi disk avalable for measument. Only light meter. Field blank performed at 15:00 MST
calm, partly cloudy
1m off bottom samples were taken at 45m - 22SWL84138. Very smokey day.

Bottom grab @ 61m (metals + Hgs)

Wind Speed: 3km/hr SW. Wave Height: <0.01m. Sunny day, checked the buoy to clean off the sensors - there was a lot of algal growth on them, saw some pelicans. There were not many boats on the lake. Someone from PLWA joined us to learn about secchi disk readings. There was a bit of cyanobacteria growth at the surface but no visible blooms. Microcystin ID: M220159. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 12km/hr W. Wave Height: 0.01m. A little windier at the beginning of the trip but calmed down when sampling the comp sites. Checked the sensors at the buoy, they had a decent amount of algae growth on the outside but the sensor tips were fairly clean. Did not see many other boats on the lake. It has been a hot week with no precipitation. Saw lots of cyanobacteria growth near the surface throughout the whole lake. Microcystin ID: M220160. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.01m. The trip started out a little windy but calmed down at the profile site. Cleaned the loggers at the buoy - they were quite clean compared to the July trip. Also changed out the sonde for AEP and kept the old guard on the new sonde - data started uploading successfully. Took AIS samples, grabbed sediment sample at profile, took QC samples. The area has not recieved much precipitation the last week. Observed streaks of cyanobacteria all through the lake and some surface scum near the volunteer's dock. Microcystin ID: M220161. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01189 and 22SWE01190.

Wind Speed: 17km/hr W. Wave Height: 0.1m. It was a very windy day, however, the sonde was able to stay fairly straight going down. Cleaned the sensors at the buoy but it was more difficult with the waves and something may have become disconnected as the data was not uploading to the site. The sensors were already quite clean and free of biological matter. One comp site was missed due to the wind and waves but enough water was collected for the bottle set. Microcystin ID: M220162. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 7km/hr W. Wave height: 0.05m. Calm day with mix of sun and clouds. Birds: pelican, osprey, gulls. Zooplankton net off by 1 meter (less). Microcystin ID: M220060. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr E. Wave height: 0.01m. Calm day. Some cyano particles on water. Few boats around. Birds: loon, pelican. Only 8 of 10 composite sites sampled (2 sites include Snug Cove and SE of boat launch). *Composite jug is not 10L. Microcystin ID: M220059. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 3km/hr S. Wave height: 0.05m. Metal sampling. Sediment sampling. Pelican, cormorant, grebe, loon. Snug Cove - shallow with weeds. Microcystin ID: M220058. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03326 and 22SWE03327.

Wind Speed: 15km/hr W. Wave Height: 0.05m. Windy conditions, lots of drift, white caps present. 1 anchor not holding boat. Omit composite sites in Snug Cove due to wind conditions. Microcystin ID: M220057. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
surface grab - metals

Wind Speed: 9km/hr SW. Wave height: <0.1m. Saw scoter ducks. Sunny and warm day, lake was very calm but murky. There was no one else on the water with us, wind levels were low. Took 7 hauls of water at comp sites which was more than enough. Depths stayed pretty consistent around 3-3.5m. Lake looked more green already - maybe some presence of cyanobacteria. Microcystiin ID: M220130. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 3km/hr SW. Wave Height: <0.01m. It rained most of the sampling trip, the sun came out near the last comp site. There was a blue-green algae advisory up near the boat launch and we observed some near the shoreline. This sampling trip showed a greater bottom depth than the June trip, likely due to the extensive amount of rain recieved in the area this month. Lots of loons, some pelicans, some goldeyes on the lake. One of the parks staff mentioned that the blue-green algae appeared right before Canada Day long weekend. Microcystin ID: M2200129. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 5km/hr W. Wave height: <0.01m. Hot, sunny morning, the lake was like glass. Lots of grebes and a swan pair, water appeared a little more brown in colour. Blue-gren algae advisory still posted but did not observe any on the trip. Parks staff said there have been a frequent amount of kayakers this month. Collected AIS, sediment and QC Samples. Microcystin ID: M220128. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01261 and 22SWE01262.

Wind Speed: 4km/hr W. Wave Height: <0.01m. Cool, calm morning on the lake. Lots of cyanobacteria present throughout the lake. Blue-green algae advisory still in place. There were no other boats on the lake. Saw some swans and ducks on the lake. Microcystin ID: M220127. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.
water fairly clear, visible zooplankton, pollen in water column. No visible algae
very windy day, white caps. unable to get accurate secchi due to wind/drift
some phytoplankton in water column
Top grab @ 1m (metals + Hgs)
Bottom grab @ 4m (metals + Hgs)

Wind Speed: 2km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.00m. Calm, cool morning, some rain drizzles. Birds: terns, cormorants. Martens. Angler surveyors visited us. Jackfish/Pike in bad shape, no minnows present, low in walleye. Zooplankton net off by 1 meter (less). Microcystin ID: M220032. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
Wind Speed: 4km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.00m. Few boaters around lake. Hot day. Cyanobacteria advisory. Birds: pelican, grebe, gulls. Microcystin ID: M220031. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 7km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.00m. Metal sampling taken. Sediment sampling taken. A dead lake whitefish spotted. 2 bald eagles sighted. Microcystin ID: M220030. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03494 and 22SWE03495.
Wind Speed: 15km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.01m. Little windy. Duckweeds on the water. Lost 3 inches of water since last month. Microcystin ID: M220029. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
surface grab - metals
Wind Speed: 11km/hr NE. Wave Height: 0.1m. Calm day. Birds: bald eagle, common loon, red necked grebe, terns. Minnows present. Microcystin ID: M220040. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
Wind Speed: 9km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.00m. Calm, sunny day. Birds: pelican, loon, gulls, red necked grebe. Shallow secchi depth at E boat launch. Microcystin ID: M220039. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.00m. Sediment sample taken. Metal sampling taken. Blue-green algae advisory in effect. Microcystin ID: M220038. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03470 and 22SWE03471.
Wind Speed: 8km/hr SE. Wave height: 0.00m. Cyano particles present. Loons, gulls. Calm day with minimal boat traffic. Microcystin ID: M220037. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.
surface grab - metals

Wind Speed: 7km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.1-0.2m. A little rougher for waves at the beginning but became calmer throughout the trip. Lots of waterfowl on lake, mostly overcast with a little sun poking through. No one else on lake. Volunteer noticed some cyanobacteria particles. Microcystin ID: M220134. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr SE. Wave Height: <0.01m. Sampling day started out sunny and calm. The wind gust picked up to around 21km/hr at the 8th comp site. Lots of cyanobacteria present in the lake and on the shore. It rained last night for about an hour. There were a few fishing boats on the lake. Did not see too many birds on the lake. Microcystin ID: M220133. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 11km/hr S. Wave Height: <0.01. Sunny, calm day on the lake. Some presence of blue-green algae - advisory is posted. A few boats on the lake. Lots of cyanobacteria present throughout the lake with higher concentrations near the west side. Observed several dead whitefish floating on the surface in this area. The cyanobacteria was thick and some scum was present in certain areas. Took AIS, sediment and QC samples. Microcystin ID: M220132. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event invovled a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01238 and 22SWE01239.

Wind Speed: 6km/hr S. Wave Height: 0.01m. Beginning of the trip there was a little lingering fog but it cleared up quickly and was sunny and warm. There were particles of cyanobacteria at the profile site and the density of cyanobacteria increased around the south to east side of the lake. Observed some scum patches on the east to north side. Saw a lot of dead whitefish on the surface starting around Williamson Park, east to north side of the lake. A couple other boats were out, not much precipitation has happened the last month. Microcystin ID: M220131. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 13km/hr NW. Wave height: <0.01m. The trip started out very sunny and the lake was calm, although it was noted that the lake was a little choppy 1 hour prior. Observed some suspended particles at the surface when sampling. Possible cyano but did not look grass like. There were a few other speedboats on the lake. Only 8/10 comp sites could be completed due to a storm coming in. The west side of the lake was sampled where a couple sites to the east were unable to be completed. Enough water was collected for the sample bottles though. Microcystin ID: M220017. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 5km/hr NW. Wave height: <0.01m. The lake was calm and quiet when the trip first began. The wind picked up a bit while sampling the comp sites. This week has been very hot and little precipitation. There were not many other boats on the lake. Observed some algae growth on the surface. The boat drifted a little while we were at a comp site so the euphotic tubing got a little sediment in it but not in the comp jug. The tubing got properly washed out. Microcystin ID: M220018. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 12km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.01m. Hot, sunny day. Did not observe any blooms or scum on surface. Clarity was pretty good. Some rec and sailboats on the lake. Collected AIS, sediment and QC samples. Area has not recieved much precipitation in the last couple weeks. Microcystin ID: M220019. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01324 and 22SWE01325.

Wind Speed: 21 km/hr W. Wave Height: 0.2m. The start of the trip was cool, drizzles of rain and a bit windy - wind picked up a bit through the sampling trip with some white caps forming near the end of the composite sampling, but the sun came out which warmed things up. The secchi depth was the lowest its been all summer. The fall has been quite warm and dry, but the area recieved some rain this morning. Did not see or hear any wildlife. Microcystin ID: M220020. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 8km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.10m. Wind began to pick up, drizzle rain. Bird: gulls. Weather escalated rapidly after using probe meter and zooplankton net. Only collected composite samples from site 1, 2, 3, 10 as wind picked up and "white caps" began to appear. Zooplankton net off by 1 meter (less). Microcystin ID: M220056. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 17km/hr SE. Wave Height: 0.3m. New profile location: 54.83713, -111.37878 (39m). Profile site, max depth, being drifted a little bit. Windy and wavy. No composite sample take in site 2 and 4. Microcystin ID: M220055. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 8km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.1m. Strong wind gusts. Metal sample. Sediment sample. Microcystin ID: M220054. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE03281 and 22SWE03282.
Wind Speed: 9km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.01m. Calm day. Cloud cover increased over time. Water level went down since last visit. Microcystin ID: M220053. Probe #: 17B103383. Net: Tow.

SampleComment: Wind Speed: 9km/hr NE. Wave Height: 0.05m. Calm day, cool in the morning but temperature increased significantly in the afternoon. Water appeared to be a little green with some cyanobacteria paticles. Microcystin ID: M220150. Probe #:17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.05m. The water was calm near Seba Beach where we left from. The waves became a little more prominent near the profile. It was a warm morning and predicted to reach +35°C in the afternoon. There were a couple other boats on the lake but they said it has been quieter this summer for rec activities so far. Observed some evidence of algae growing near the surface. Microcystin ID: M220149. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 24km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.2m. Very windy day, caused some issues with putting equipment straight down in the water, sunny and warm though. Had to miss 2 comp sites due to difficulty navigating through waves. Collected all 3 AIS samples, collected sediment sample at profile. Did not observe any cyanobacteria blooms and water clarity was fairly high. Collected some milfoil samples at the sailing club dock. Saw some pelicans. Could be some issues with the data at 6.5m - 8.0m due to high winds. Microcystin ID: M220148. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01168 and 22SWE01169.

Wind Speed: 9km/hr SW. Wave Height: <0.05m. Lake was very calm at the profile site. Wind picked up to 12km/hr through the comp sites. It was a little hazy in the sky, the sun looked red before sampling began and some smoke was smelt. There was only a couple fishing boats on the lake. There was some cyanobacteria particles in the water but no streaks or blooms except near the south Seba Yatch Club docks where we departed from. Microcystin ID: M220147. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 5km/hr SE. Wave Height: <0.01m. Overcast day but no rain. Lake was very calm and there were no other boats. Significant amount of pollen on surface. Collected water mites in the zooplankton sample. Tons of Franklin's gulls on the water and some pelicans. Microcystin ID: M220138. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 13km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.01m. Sunny and calm when we started sampling. We got some brief periods of rain when we started the composite sites but mostly remained overcast. Observed a lot of algae cover near the boat launch and cyanobacteria in the entirety of the lake. It had rained in the area the last few days. The hose off of the tow net bucket got clogged a couple times while collecting AIS samples with all the plant material. Saw some pelicans, ducks and lots of black terns. Microcystin ID: M220137. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 17km/hr SW. Wave Height: 0.01m. A little bit of a windy day. The lake was a little choppy but calmed down near the end. Lots of cyanobacteria present throughout the lake. There were a couple other boats on the lake. There was a blue green algae advisory posted at the boat launch but did not observe any near shore. Saw some pelicans, terns, and a bald eagle. Took AIS, sediment and QC samples. Microcystin ID: M220136. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01225 and 22SWE01226.

Wind Speed: 6km/hr E. Wave Height: 0.01m. It was a little hazy in the sky but there was no sign of smoke. There were no other boats on the lake. There were particles of cyanobacteria at the surface but did not look as concentrated as the August trip. The area has not recieved much precipitation the last couple weeks. Microcystin ID: M220135. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.
Wind Speed: 10km/hr S. Wave height: 0.05m. Calm day, saw some pelicans. Not too busy on the lake. Warm morning, little to no cloud cover. Microcystin ID: M220158. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 13km/hr NW. Wave Height: 0.05m. Saw a bald eagle and its nest on the west side. Water level relatively high. A larger number of small particles in the water column. Pelican population on the incline. Microcystin ID: M220156. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.

Wind Speed: 6km/hr SW. Wave Height: <0.01m. Overcast day on the lake with a sprinkle of rain. There was a couple of other boats out. Volunteer said the lake has been a lot quieter than previous years. Completed AIS sampling, QC sampling, and sediment sampling for AIS eDNA. There was no visible blooms of cyanobacteria. Saw some loons and ducks. To be noted that the volunteer thought the sediment from the bottom of the lake contains coal and when released back into the lake, the sample dispersed like gas would in water. Microcystin ID: M220155. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow. Sampling event involved a TP True Split Triplicate QC - QC Samples 22SWE01120 and 22SWE01121.

Wind Speed: 7km/hr W. Wave Height: <0.05m. The lake was very calm while we were loading up the boat but the wind picked up to 16km/hr gusts, at profile. There was a more significant presence of cyanobacteria blooms throughout the lake this month and water clarity was low. The lake was heavily used over the long weekend by rec boats. There was only one other boat out today. Microcystin ID: M220157. Probe #: 17K104466. Net: Tow.
